{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.prod: \".net-framework\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"dotnet-clr\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nms.assetid: 5bad60aa-6084-4c7b-aefd-9b581f04382e\ncaps.latest.revision: 6\nauthor: \"BrucePerlerMS\"\nms.author: \"bruceper\"\nmanager: \"mbaldwin\"\n---\n# Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures\nCounter name: Security Validation and Authentication Failures  \n  \n## Description  \n This counter is incremented whenever a message is rejected due to a security problem not covered by the \"Security Calls Not Authorized\" counter. Such problems include:  \n  \n-   Client token cannot be read from the message.  \n  \n-   Client token has failed authentication (bad password).  \n  \n-   Signature verification has failed (the message has been tampered).  \n  \n-   The message is a duplicate from a previous one, which can happen during a replay attack.  \n  \n-   A decryption failure has occurred.  \n  \n-   Some required elements (missing timestamp or encrypted data block) are missing from the message.  \n  \n-   Errors have occurred during TLSNEGO/SPNEGO handshake.","nodes":[{"pos":[12,86],"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,74]}]},{"pos":[395,452],"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","linkify":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","nodes":[{"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","pos":[0,57]}]},{"content":"Counter name: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","pos":[453,514]},{"pos":[523,534],"content":"Description","linkify":"Description","nodes":[{"content":"Description","pos":[0,11]}]},{"content":"This counter is incremented whenever a message is rejected due to a security problem not covered by the \"Security Calls Not Authorized\" counter.","pos":[538,682]},{"content":"Such problems include:","pos":[683,705]},{"content":"Client token cannot be read from the message.","pos":[715,760]},{"content":"Client token has failed authentication (bad password).","pos":[770,824]},{"content":"Signature verification has failed (the message has been tampered).","pos":[834,900]},{"content":"The message is a duplicate from a previous one, which can happen during a replay attack.","pos":[910,998]},{"content":"A decryption failure has occurred.","pos":[1008,1042]},{"content":"Some required elements (missing timestamp or encrypted data block) are missing from the message.","pos":[1052,1148]},{"content":"Errors have occurred during TLSNEGO/SPNEGO handshake.","pos":[1158,1211]}]}